[{"client_msg_id":"f28be0db-c013-44de-b66a-a42f2ff024e5","type":"message","text":"Is there a cleaner way to write something like this:\n```map(y -&gt; foo(x, y), [1, 2, 3])```\nOr when chaining iterators:\n```Iterators.product(1:3, 1:3) |&gt; x -&gt; Iterators.take(x, 5)```\nDefining anon functions works fine, but with the guidance to avoid x -&gt; f(x) in the style guide, I wondered if there was a different way","user":"U01E7DK9HPA","ts":"1609874304.315700","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"a9=zM","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Is there a cleaner way to write something like this:\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"map(y -> foo(x, y), [1, 2, 3])"}]},{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"\nOr when chaining iterators:\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Iterators.product(1:3, 1:3) |> x -> Iterators.take(x, 5)"}]},{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"\nDefining anon functions works fine, but with the guidance to avoid x -> f(x) in the style guide, I wondered if there was a different way"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609874304.315700","reply_count":7,"reply_users_count":2,"latest_reply":"1609874577.317300","reply_users":["USU9FRPEU","U8D9768Q6"],"subscribed":false},{"client_msg_id":"393bddcb-0e70-4144-99cd-e4a46196194b","type":"message","text":"What is `x`?","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609874329.315800","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"yat","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What is "},{"type":"text","text":"x","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":"?"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609874304.315700","parent_user_id":"U01E7DK9HPA"},{"client_msg_id":"31c3d320-1104-4c4a-a498-301ee56c531f","type":"message","text":"in the first syntax?","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609874347.316000","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"O5e","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"in the first syntax?"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609874304.315700","parent_user_id":"U01E7DK9HPA"},{"client_msg_id":"7c0934d5-a75a-4f86-b113-3ab995ce1a9c","type":"message","text":"The style guide says to avoid `x -&gt; f(x)` because it's literally the same as `f` but more work for the compiler.","user":"U8D9768Q6","ts":"1609874382.316200","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"w3Vd","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The style guide says to avoid "},{"type":"text","text":"x -> f(x)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" because it's literally the same as "},{"type":"text","text":"f","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" but more work for the compiler."}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609874304.315700","parent_user_id":"U01E7DK9HPA","reactions":[{"name":"point_up","users":["U680THK2S"],"count":1}]},{"client_msg_id":"9480fbce-6e8d-453c-a97e-5d213554777a","type":"message","text":"`y -&gt; f(x, y)` is totally fine.","user":"U8D9768Q6","ts":"1609874400.316400","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"SN0b","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"y -> f(x, y)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is totally fine."}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609874304.315700","parent_user_id":"U01E7DK9HPA"},{"client_msg_id":"b3a1e0c0-380b-4891-86a8-a16a1830385e","type":"message","text":"`Base.Fix1` or `Base.Fix2` could be useful.\n```julia&gt; foo(x,y) = x + y\nfoo (generic function with 1 method)\n\njulia&gt; f = Base.Fix1(foo, 10)\n(::Base.Fix1{typeof(foo),Int64}) (generic function with 1 method)\n\njulia&gt; f.([1,2,3])\n3-element Array{Int64,1}:\n 11\n 12\n 13```","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609874442.316800","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"pev1","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Base.Fix1","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","text":"Base.Fix2","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" could be useful.\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"julia> foo(x,y) = x + y\nfoo (generic function with 1 method)\n\njulia> f = Base.Fix1(foo, 10)\n(::Base.Fix1{typeof(foo),Int64}) (generic function with 1 method)\n\njulia> f.([1,2,3])\n3-element Array{Int64,1}:\n 11\n 12\n 13"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609874304.315700","parent_user_id":"U01E7DK9HPA"},{"client_msg_id":"dde5f062-96f3-49eb-991e-864a2b8633aa","type":"message","text":"What I like about `Fix1` or `Fix2` is that one can still figure out what the original function was.","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609874523.317100","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"kcZF4","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What I like about "},{"type":"text","text":"Fix1","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","text":"Fix2","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is that one can still figure out what the original function was."}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609874304.315700","parent_user_id":"U01E7DK9HPA"},{"client_msg_id":"858a7321-d457-4cd6-8295-14cb9ef41b37","type":"message","text":"```julia&gt; f.f\nfoo (generic function with 1 method)\n\njulia&gt; f.x\n10```","user":"USU9FRPEU","ts":"1609874577.317300","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"Ez+0","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"julia> f.f\nfoo (generic function with 1 method)\n\njulia> f.x\n10"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1609874304.315700","parent_user_id":"U01E7DK9HPA"}]